---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Navan Hart" description="A rare memory animal of Vaelinya.">
  <section class="page-section animal-sheet-page">
    <article class="panel animal-sheet">
      <div class="animal-sheet-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">World · Animals</p>
        <h1>Navan Hart</h1>
        <p class="lede">A rare deerlike memory animal that appears where a place has remembered a truth clearly enough to begin healing.</p>

        <dl class="animal-facts">
          <div>
            <dt>What it is</dt>
            <dd>A rare memory animal and witness animal. It is not a pet, monster, or ordinary deer; its appearance means something has been remembered truthfully.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Where it appears</dt>
            <dd>Old road bends, forest glades, quiet path stones, soft mist, remembered places, and ground where hidden truth has begun to return.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>How to recognise it</dt>
            <dd>Look for a deep warm brown body, moon-white antlers, calm dark eyes, small route-marks along the neck, and a quiet old-road presence.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Sound and movement</dt>
            <dd>It is almost silent. Its hooves make a soft double step, even when it walks alone, as if memory is walking beside it.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>What it means</dt>
            <dd>It appears only where memory has been carried truthfully rather than hidden, denied, or wasted. Its appearance means healing can begin.</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>

        <p class="access-note"><strong>Accessibility note:</strong> The Navan Hart is a rare deerlike animal with moon-white antlers, calm dark eyes, route-marks along its neck, and a quiet double step.</p>

        <nav class="animal-links" aria-label="Related Navan Hart pages">
          <a href="/artefacts/symbols/navan/">NAVAN symbol</a>
          <a href="/world/warm-remembering/">Warm Remembering</a>
          <a href="/world/animals/">Animals of Vaelinya</a>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <figure class="animal-sheet-art animal-sheet-art-tall">
        <picture>
          <source
            media="(max-width: 560px)"
            srcset="/assets/images/vaelinya/animals/navan-hart-v01-512-q.png"
          />
          <source
            media="(max-width: 900px)"
            srcset="/assets/images/vaelinya/animals/navan-hart-v01-768-q.png"
          />
          <img
            src="/assets/images/vaelinya/animals/navan-hart-v01-1024-q.png"
            alt="Navan Hart, a rare deerlike memory animal with a deep warm brown body, moon-white antlers, calm dark eyes, small route-marks along its neck, and a quiet old-road presence."
            loading="eager"
            decoding="async"
            width="1024"
            height="1287"
          />
        </picture>
        <figcaption>A Navan Hart with moon-white antlers, route-marks, and a quiet old-road presence.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </article>
  </section>

  <style>
    :global(.site-main) {
      max-width: none;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .animal-sheet-page {
      position: relative;
      isolation: isolate;
      overflow: hidden;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: clamp(1.2rem, 3vw, 2.6rem) 1rem;
      border: 0;
      border-radius: 0;
      background: transparent;
      box-shadow: none;
    }

    .animal-sheet-page::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      z-index: -2;
      background-image:
        radial-gradient(circle at 58% 16%, rgba(241, 239, 226, 0.22), transparent 34%),
        linear-gradient(rgba(16, 17, 20, 0.12), rgba(16, 17, 20, 0.46)),
        url('/assets/images/vaelinya/animals/navan-hart-habitat-v01-1920.jpg');
      background-repeat: no-repeat;
      background-position: center top;
      background-size: cover;
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .animal-sheet-page::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      top: clamp(0.75rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
      bottom: clamp(0.75rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
      left: 50%;
      width: min(calc(100% - 2rem), 1180px);
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      z-index: -1;
      border-radius: 1.9rem;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.66);
      background: rgba(248, 246, 250, 0.12);
      box-shadow:
        inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.44),
        inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.18),
        0 22px 54px rgba(8, 5, 20, 0.34);
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .animal-sheet {
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      width: min(100%, 1120px);
      margin-inline: auto;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.18fr) minmax(300px, 0.82fr);
      gap: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
      align-items: start;
      padding: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
      background: linear-gradient(
        180deg,
        rgba(248, 246, 250, 0.92),
        rgba(248, 246, 250, 0.9)
      );
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.62);
      box-shadow:
        inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.54),
        0 16px 42px rgba(8, 5, 20, 0.28);
      backdrop-filter: blur(6px) saturate(1.03);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(6px) saturate(1.03);
    }

    .animal-sheet-copy,
    .animal-sheet-art {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
    }

    .animal-sheet .lede {
      max-width: 56ch;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .animal-facts {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.75rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    .animal-facts div {
      padding-block: 0.65rem;
      border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink, #211a33) 14%, transparent);
    }

    .animal-facts dt {
      margin-bottom: 0.18rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: var(--ink, #211a33);
    }

    .animal-facts dd {
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .access-note {
      margin: 1rem 0 0;
      padding: 0.75rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink, #211a33) 14%, transparent);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .animal-links {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.55rem;
      margin-top: 0.85rem;
    }

    .animal-links a {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      min-height: 40px;
      padding: 0.55rem 0.85rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: color-mix(in srgb, #fff4be 82%, white);
      border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ink, #211a33) 14%, transparent);
      font-weight: 750;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .animal-sheet-art {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background: transparent;
      border: 0;
    }

    .animal-sheet-art img {
      display: block;
      width: min(100%, 390px);
      height: auto;
      margin-inline: auto;
      filter:
        drop-shadow(0 0 18px rgba(225, 209, 168, 0.18))
        drop-shadow(0 22px 34px rgba(22, 14, 39, 0.22));
    }

    .animal-sheet-art figcaption {
      max-width: 36ch;
      margin: 0.45rem auto 0;
      color: var(--muted, #574d68);
      font-size: 0.86rem;
      line-height: 1.45;
      text-align: center;
    }

    @media (min-width: 1060px) {
      .animal-facts {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
        column-gap: 1.25rem;
        row-gap: 0.4rem;
      }

      .animal-facts div {
        padding-block: 0.55rem;
      }

      .animal-facts div:nth-child(5) {
        grid-column: 1 / -1;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .animal-sheet {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .animal-sheet-art {
        order: -1;
      }

      .animal-sheet-art img {
        width: min(100%, 360px);
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 820px) {
      .animal-sheet-page {
        padding: clamp(0.75rem, 3.5vw, 1.2rem) 0.75rem;
      }

      .animal-sheet-page::before {
        background-image:
          radial-gradient(circle at 58% 16%, rgba(241, 239, 226, 0.2), transparent 34%),
          linear-gradient(rgba(16, 17, 20, 0.14), rgba(16, 17, 20, 0.5)),
          url('/assets/images/vaelinya/animals/navan-hart-habitat-v01-1280.jpg');
        background-position: center top;
      }

      .animal-sheet-page::after {
        width: min(calc(100% - 1.5rem), 1120px);
        border-radius: 1.35rem;
        border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
        background: rgba(248, 246, 250, 0.16);
      }

      .animal-sheet {
        background: linear-gradient(
          180deg,
          rgba(248, 246, 250, 0.94),
          rgba(248, 246, 250, 0.92)
        );
        backdrop-filter: blur(6px) saturate(1.03);
        -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(6px) saturate(1.03);
      }

      .animal-sheet-art img {
        width: min(100%, 330px);
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
